PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776265866
OL,3,CSouth East Water 'should have acted
OL,4,Cquicker' to deal with warning sign of
OL,5,Coutage
OL,7,FSouth East Water's Chief Executive
OL,8,FDavid Hinton has admitted that the
OL,9,Fcompany "should have acted quicker" on
OL,10,Fthe "early warning signs" of problems
OL,11,Fat the Pembury water treatment works
OL,12,Flast year.
OL,14,FMr Hinton told the Environment, Food
OL,15,Fand Rural Affairs Committee that when
OL,16,FSEW did start to respond it was "too
OL,17,Fslow and unstructured".
OL,26,@qD@IOUqD@cO]rD@EOUrD@YO]xD@aOUyD@VO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/13
